article.headline: Princeton 76, Cornell 68 (2OT)
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Noah Savage scored 28 points and Scott Greenman added 27 to lead Princeton over Cornell 76-68 in double overtime on Friday night. Greenman hit 3-pointers with one second remaining to force both overtimes, then the Tigers (8-13, 6-2 Ivy) outscored Cornell 12-4 in the second overtime for the win. Savage made six 3-pointers as Princeton shot 50 percent for the game. Ryan Rourke, Lenny Collins and Adam Gore each had 14 points for the Big Red (10-13, 5-4). Andrew Naeve grabbed 10 rebounds. Cornell shot just 31 percent after halftime and missed all five 3-pointers and four free throws in the overtime periods.
